Interface TileCache.ReadCallback

    TileCache
    public static interface TileCache.ReadCallback
    The callback interface for tile reading.

    • Method Detail

      • canceled

        boolean canceled()
        Returns a flag indicating whether or not the read has been canceled. This allows for asynchronously cancelling a read that is currently processing.
        Returns:
        true if the read should be canceled, false otherwise.

      • update

        void update​(int dstX,
            int dstY,
            int dstW,
            int dstH,
            byte[] pixelData,
            int off,
            int len)
        This method is invoked when a region of the requested tile has been read.
        Parameters:
        dstX - The x-coordinate of the tile that corresponds to the first pixel in pixelData
        dstY - The y-coordinate of the tile that corresponds to the first pixel in pixelData
        dstW - The width, in pixels, of the region of the tile to be updated with pixelData
        dstH - The height, in pixels, of the region of the tile to be updated with pixelData
        pixelData - The pixel data (in the same format as returned by the read method of the configured com.atakmap.TileReader.tilesets.TileReader.
        off - The offset into the pixelData array of the first pixel
        len - The number of bytes in pixelData that contain the update data
